$interpreted: Hutchinson: Sophie, are you sure we want to do this?
Sophie: If the headmaster isn’t willing to help, the Queen is Elio’s cousin...we’ve got no choice but to ask for her help!
Soldier: This is the Kingdom of the Sun’s encampment. No snooping around!
Sophie: Please! Let us see the Queen! Elio’s been kidnapped and only the Queen can save him!
Soldier: We’re busy as all hell! We’ve got no time to listen to this blibber-blabber! Leave, immediately! Otherwise, don’t blame us for what happens!
Sophie: If you don’t let me see the Queen, then I’m not going anywhere!
Jerome: What’s going on?
Soldier: Officer Muca, this group of stragglers is clambering to see the Queen. No matter what we do, they just won’t leave!
Jerome: You want to see the Queen? What’s the reason?
Sophie: Elio Ceres...he’s the Queen’s cousin?
Sophie: We know where he is...we hope the Queen can help him...
Jerome: ……
Jerome: If what you’re saying is true, then we...
Jerome: We must find Elio and arrest him!
Sophie: Arrest...arrest him!?
Jerome: Elio is a traitor who helped the false king. If we catch him...
Jerome: We must interrogate him to find out Theodore’s whereabouts!
Ru-yi: Sophie, forget it! They want to interrogate Elio!
Hutchinson: They want to hurt Elio!
Sophie: What should I do...Elio...he’s...
Ru-yi: In any case, let’s get out of here!
Hanbei: Hey, Mr. Soldier. Apologies, we made a mistake.
Hanbei: We’ll get out of your hair immediately!
Soldier: ...Officer, are we just going to let them get away scotch free?
Jerome: Schemers like this, making up nonsense just to get a reward, you’ll never catch them all. They’re just a bunch of liars.
Jerome: This is of utmost importance. First, find the Queen, understood?
Soldier: Yes, sir!
